## The Silent Converter

Remember studying `Truthy` and `Falsy`? The `if` statement relies on it completely!

When you put a value inside the `if ()` condition, JavaScript automatically, silently runs `Boolean()` on it.

```javascript
let userName = "Alice";

if (userName) {
  console.log("Hello Alice!"); 
}
```

Because `"Alice"` is a Truthy value, the block executes! This is incredibly common for checking if a variable exists before using it.
